The pytest-lazy-fixture plugin makes possible to use a fixtures inside `pytest.mark.parametrize`:

```python
@pytest.fixture(params=[1, 2])
def one(request):
    return request.param

@pytest.mark.parametrize('arg1,arg2', [
    ('val1', pytest.lazy_fixture('one')),
])
def test_func(arg1, arg2):
    assert arg2 in [1, 2]
```

If this example, `deadfixtures` doesn't detect the fixture `one` being used and returns the warning.

Ref: There is a proposal in Pytest to make this behavior possible out of the box: https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/proposals/parametrize_with_fixtures.html

